title: Square, late 19th–early 20th century
description: Five sheer piña cloth squares with plain circular central field. Border of corners filled with symmetrical scrolling flowers, stems, leaves, in Chinese style, formed by white shadow embroidery. On outer borders, narrow inset of drawn work and embroidered edge of plain piña cloth.
